snippet: One of a dozen Florida A&M University students now charged with manslaughter in the hazing death of a drum major plans to plead guilty in the hope of receiving a more lenient sentence.
abstract: Caleb Jackson, one of a dozen Florida A&M University students charged with manslaughter in hazing death of drum major Robert Champion, plans to plead guilty in hope of receiving a more lenient sentence.
lead_paragraph: One of a dozen Florida A&M University students now charged with manslaughter in the hazing death of a drum major plans to plead guilty in the hope of receiving a more lenient sentence.

headline.main: Florida: Guilty Plea Expected in Hazing Death of Drum Major
